About 2 weeks ago I mentioned I had amazing news that I could share soon, I’m THRILLED to be able to officially announce: 

“As a brand that has advocated for the inclusion of ‘All Ages, All Races, All Genders’ since it’s inception, MAC is proud to stand with all those fighting for racial justice and equality around the world.  Last June, the brand re committed to it’s core mantra through a series of global commitments to better address the racial inequities facing MAC’s black employees, consumers, and communities.

To support those commitments, on February 1, MAC announced the formation of The MAC Movement — a new employee advisory board created to mobilize the Global MAC team around the brand’s diversity, equity, and inclusion efforts and advise the brand on injustice issues both internally and externally.”

I’m humbled and honored to be one of 8 employees selected in North America to become an inaugural member of such incredible and important MAC history. 

I am the only artist in advisory, in collaboration with the incomparable legend that is @romerojennings , our Director of Makeup Artistry.

My personal platform in this experience is to be a voice for those that don’t always have the privilege of being consistently heard in the beauty industry, working diligently with the brand to create greater visibility in campaigns, combatting micro aggressions in the workplace, and ensure greater representation across all levels of the organization.

Beauty is my vehicle, but people...are my purpose. 

To all the dreamers out there, keep dreaming, your gift will surely always make room for you💫

Ok, who’s missing their holiday fix?

Although this little guy seems happy, the Balinese are doing it tough.

80% of people in Bali rely on tourism, whether directly or indirectly. This year, they’ve been hit hard. 

Last year, more than 6 million tourists travelled to Bali. Over 1 million of them were Australian. 2020 has told a different story. 

A friend reached out to me yesterday asking for my help, and this is not the first time this has happened.

You can help too.

Rosacea Awareness Month
.
Check out my blog post to find out more about this inflammatory skin disease often presenting itself as redness and broken capillaries across the centre of the face, cheeks, nose and sometimes between the eyebrows and onto the forehead. 
.
Rosacea is commonly passed to us through genetics but can also be worsened by skin damage, like unsuitable skincare, sun damage or environment factors.
.
In this blog I talk about Rosacea, help you understand the skin condition better and give you advice regarding good skincare routines to help calm and soothe your skin. 
.
Plus looking at lifestyle changes to improve the health of your skin. 
.
In many cases, I have decreased the symptoms and strengthened my client's skin barrier to help calm and reduce future flare-ups.
.

Bref c’est une crème un peu riche, super agréable à utiliser et qui n’est pas trop lourde sur la peau. Elle est enveloppante, crémeuse, douce et elle sent bon. Si vous avez la barrière cutanée endommagée ou la peau sèche c’est une super addition à votre routine. C’est la crème que j’ai utilisé dans ma routine post-peeling !

PS : elle contient des peptides qui sont des composés chimiques formés d’acides aminés qui fonctionnent en envoyant des signaux aux cellules de la peau pour augmenter la production de collagène et d'élastine, ce qui peut aider à réduire l'apparence des rides et ridules, améliorer la texture de la peau et lui donner un aspect plus ferme. Ils peuvent également aider à améliorer l'hydratation de la peau, à réduire l'inflammation et à protéger la peau. Bref il y’a différents types de peptides quai sont choisit en fonction de ce qu’ils peuvent apporter à la peau.

Reviewing common skin toxicities related to chemotherapy treatment! 

1️⃣ Acneform Rash
2️⃣ Folliculitis
3️⃣ Hyperpigmentation
4️⃣ Hand & Foot Syndrome 

I often see these in my practice and yes-they typically resolve after treatment! We are lucky to have an oncologic dermatologist in our cancer center who is very helpful in managing and treating these conditions. 

If you are experiencing any of the conditions mentioned definitely speak to your oncology team. Fortunately most of these conditions resolve after chemotherapy but you may need intervention while experiencing these side effects. 

DM me with questions or share your stories below! 

You can also visit our website for additional information and product recommendations.

AviClear is an FDA-approved laser that treats mild to severe acne by targeting the source of acne without the use of topical or oral acne medications.

This is a unique laser technology because of the wavelength it uses, which selectively targets the oil glands (sebaceous glands) in the skin. 

We are the first clinic in the Northwest Arkansas to offer this acne laser treatment.

The laser improves your acne over the course of three monthly treatments, each of which is about 30 minutes in duration. It is safe for all skin types and tones and there is very minimal downtime after treatment.

This treatment is only offered in our Fayetteville location currently.

Start with a consultation. Links to book a consult and learn more about AviClear are in our profile.

Rosacea Awareness Month
.
Check out my blog post to find out more about this inflammatory skin disease often presenting itself as redness and broken capillaries across the centre of the face, cheeks, nose and sometimes between the eyebrows and onto the forehead. 
.
Rosacea is commonly passed to us through genetics but can also be worsened by skin damage, like unsuitable skincare, sun damage or environment factors.
.
In this blog I talk about Rosacea, help you understand the skin condition better and give you advice regarding good skincare routines to help calm and soothe your skin. 
.
Plus looking at lifestyle changes to improve the health of your skin. 
.
In many cases, I have decreased the symptoms and strengthened my client's skin barrier to help calm and reduce future flare-ups.
.

"Skincare 101: Do's and Don'ts for Your Daily Routine! 💆‍♀️✨🌿⁣⁣"

Hey beauties! 💕 Taking care of your skin is a must for a healthy and glowing complexion. Here are some simple do's and don'ts to keep in mind for your daily skincare routine:

Do’s:

Cleanse your face twice a day with a gentle cleanser to remove dirt, makeup, and impurities.

Exfoliate 1-2 times a week to slough off dead skin cells and unclog pores.
Moisturize daily to keep your skin hydrated and nourished.

Apply sunscreen with at least SPF 30 to protect your skin from harmful UV rays.
Remove your makeup before going to bed to allow your skin to breathe and regenerate overnight.

Drink plenty of water to keep your skin hydrated from within.

DON'Ts:

Don't sleep with your makeup on as it can clog pores and lead to breakouts.

Avoid using harsh or abrasive scrubs that can damage your skin barrier.

Don't forget to patch test new skincare products before applying them all over your face to avoid potential allergic reactions.

Avoid touching your face with dirty hands to prevent transferring bacteria to your skin.

Don't over-exfoliate or use too many active ingredients at once, as it can cause irritation and damage to your skin.

Remember, consistency is key in skincare! Follow these do's and don'ts for a simple and effective daily routine. 🌟✨ #SkincareTips #SkincareRoutine #HealthySkin #GlowingSkin #SkincareDoandDonts

✨ANTIQUE VELVET✨

El look de hoy es muy especial, he podido contar con las manos de @paquicastro que es maquilladora en @macduquesevilla y WoW. No puedo estar más contenta con el resultado.

Ella me preguntó que qué me apetecía y lo cierto es que quería un look bien potente, de estos que no pasan desapercibidos. ¡Y creo que lo hemos conseguido!

Mil gracias Paqui por tu dedicación, entender lo que buscaba a la perfección y por hacer un makeup tan tan chulo🤍.

Y ahora, vamos con los detalles del look:

👁️SOMBRAS

Las sombras protagonistas son de la paleta It's Designer de @maccosmetics_es que es espectacular. 
High Concept es la plateada, Triennial Wave la azul eléctrico que lleva la base y Gallerina la azul pavo real para potenciar la anterior.

Tenéis una reseña de la paleta It's Designer y merece muchísimo la pena, es brutal 🔥.

💄LABIAL

El labial que he elegido es el ANTIQUE VELVET de @maccosmetics_es y da nombre al look. Es un marrón chocolate casi negro increíble. He querido añadir una foto sonriendo para que veáis cómo resalta el blanco de los dientes, una pasada.

Es de la gama de los mate, así que como siempre os digo la duración, pigmentación y confort están garantizados.

🥰COLORETE

El que ha elegido @paquicastro es el WARM SOUL de @maccosmetics_es y me ha encantado la sintonía que se crea con él. Para un look tan potente es perfecto.

✏️MASCARA DE PESTAÑAS

La In Extreme Dimension ha sido la elegida y es que es una maravilla. No llevo pestañas postizas ni extensiones ni nada, solo la máscara. ¿Es o no increíble? 🥰

Me ha encantado la experiencia y ya estoy deseando repetir. Se aprende mucho cuando nos maquilla otra persona 🥰.

⁉️¿Qué os ha parecido?

👁️¡Os leo!

O primeiro tapete vermelho para valer do ano - o do #sagawards2022, que aconteceu ontem - trouxe uma leva de batons coral para os holofotes. Tivemos @jessicachastain, #cateblanchett, @naomiwatts, @reesewitherspoon e @ladygaga usando variações do tom, todas com beauty looks belíssimos! Algumas preferiram um coral mais candy, clarinho; outras apostaram em uma variação um pouco mais viva. Todas foram um sucesso! E já que estamos começando a semana falando de tendência de maquiagem, vale registrar as sombras de Jessica e de Lady Gaga. As duas usaram nuances frosted, aquelas cintilantes com aspecto gelado. O efeito está em alta, sabiam? Não sei se curto sempre, mas nelas, achei que ficou incrível. 'Universal truth'. 
It's what they settled to call it. 
Unaware, that TO EACH, HIS OWN!
The depths of my mind, 
Unclear, no traces, no signs. 
Perplexed emotions, unidentified.
To myself, I remain unknown.

They don't see what you see.
Yet, you're caught up in the hope, that they do!
A hundred claim to get you, 
& they do! 
To the very best of you! 

Blinded by what we see; 
Confusing illusions for
All that's "meant to be!"

Skeptics about our own beliefs;
Fighting one another,
Drifting through chaos, to find peace
Wanting to be right, now brings us relief. 
(sigh) 

Told them, their thoughts chimed with mine! 
So, they loved me for who I wasn't, & I took that, because for differences to live with, 
Nobody's got the time.

I'm more there, than here; 
They don't see it, & that's fine. 

Now, I write about these differences,
With my thoughts flooding reality! 
No common ground left for truth;
Our truth has become insanity.

(1) At some point in the latter half of 2016, a fishing vessel is constructed at Taipei, Taiwan and is given the name Hsiang Ching! Not to be confused with the very similar Hsiang Man Ching, built shortly afterwards. Once ready for service at the start of 2017, she comes in at 973 gross tons, has a length of 215 feet (65.8 meters), and can reportedly make around 14.5 knots. Hsiang Ching enjoys a relatively peaceful career going forward, traveling into the open Pacific for her catch. This usually entails a full freezer of Neon Flying Squid, Japanese Flying Squid, and Pacific Saury. The latter is the most often hunted for during Hsiang Ching’s cruises into the vast, blue ocean. Her crew, generally numbering between fifty to sixty-four, are able to haul aboard fifty tons worth of sea life for the markets back home. During the late months of 2022, the fishing vessel is on another voyage to catch Pacific Saury, only forty-nine crew on this occasion. As Hsiang Ching is traveling roughly 250 nautical miles east of the Kuril Islands north of Japan, around noon of November 6th, a fire is discovered aboard the fishing vessel. It rapidly spreads amidships and aft, traveling upwards until reaching the main deck. Hsiang Ching’s crew immediately take to life saving measures once the situation becomes untenable and launch several life rafts. A distress flare is fired during the abandonment process and, with great luck, a fellow squid boat is in the near vicinity. Captain Li Xinyang, of the fishing vessel Yong Fa 1 (Photo 5), takes notice of the smoke on the horizon and then the flare that shoots up nearby. He brings up all of his crew to stand by and orders the engines to full so to reach the scene as quickly as possible. All aboard Yong Fa 1 work diligently in bringing up Hsiang Ching’s crew from the life rafts. The survivors seem shaken, but are grateful to have been picked up in such a timely manner. Many are soaking wet from having fallen overboard trying to reach the rafts earlier. Others breathe a sigh of relief being aboard a vessel not on fire. Had Yong Fa 1 not been so near, they would have spent a night or more out in this weather. ((Continues Below👇))

Time to fishing #longliner #fishing #fishingboat

Won't lie, been feeling depressed and anxious, and then tornado warnings Friday. It's basically a whole mood, but at least I've got garden starts going, for whenever the weather stabilizes. 

So, I thought I'd work a theme, featuring some podcast that are both fascinating, eye opening, and deeply depressing.

So! Let's talk about The Outlaw Ocean from @ian_urbina , @latimes , and @cbcpodcasts .

The Outlaw Ocean is a non-fiction investigative journalism podcast all about the horrifying things that take place in international waters. Too big to police and under murky a jurisdiction to enforce, the distant waters are truly when bad things can happen. From large commercial vessels murdering subsistence fisherman, human trafficking, enslaved people on long-term deep sea fishing and processing facilities that can stay out to sea for years on end with supply runs from smaller ships; fed amphetamines to keep them working for days on end, living in abysmal conditions. These fish wind up in unexpected places.

You'll find one of the many ways in which cruise ships are depressingly the worst way to travel. The "magic pipe" they use when they're in unaffiliated waters to avoid paying to expell their waste at port.

Our host and founder of The Outlaw Ocean Project has spent years of his life tracking and documenting high crimes taking place in what amounts to a legal dead zone. Even going so far as to "buy back" a man's "indenture" to a fishing boat when he sees him dazed and injured, chained to the hull by his neck to keep him upright.

How will he recover? Or has he been too traumatized to return to his previous life? Time will tell.

Are you ready to learn about all this and more? Welp that's 7, 30-60 minute episodes.

**Trigger warning** I don't typically do these, but the first episode--esp. if you speak Chinese--contains the audio of a Chinese commercial fishing crew mercilessly murdering a small boat and laughing about it. 

So, if you listen to investigative journalism, like Someone Knows Something and Richest Hill, then The Outlaw Ocean is for you!

In primavera gli occhi si possono danneggiare per l’esposizione ai raggi Ultra Violetti (UV). E poi capitano giornate di vento pazzesco con terra, sabbia e polvere che ti colpisce negli occhi! Anche il polline può dare fastidio agli occhi.

Ecco i nostri consigli per te.

Indossa occhiali da sole che abbiano una protezione completa dai raggi UV. L’etichetta dovrebbe indicare: "100% di protezione UV" oppure "UV400".
Se lavori vicino a fonti d’acqua o liquidi o dove ci sono molte superfici metalliche scegli delle lenti polarizzate perché riducono il riverbero dei raggi solari proprio su queste superfici. Così la tua vista sarà più chiara e gli occhi si affaticheranno di meno.
E poi… sarà buffo, ma gli occhiali “da sole” funzionano anche quando il cielo è coperto.

“Ma così ti rendi ridicola Eli!”
“Ma figurati!”

Infatti i raggi UV penetrano attraverso le nuvole e possono provocare danni agli occhi!

Ed ora ecco un consiglio specifico per tutti gli sportivi: se pratichi sport all'aperto devi sapere che le lenti intercambiabili si adattino alle diverse condizioni di luce.

Ah, una cosa che non piacerà ai nostri follower: meglio gli occhiali con montature comode. Infatti, se li indossi a lungo ti potrebbero anche ferire le orecchie.

“Perché questa cosa non piace ai nostri follower?”
“Perché fra bellezza e utilità… scelgono sempre la bellezza!”
“E hanno ragione!”

Infine, attenzione, attenzione: vi suggeriamo di non condividere mai gli occhiali da sole con altre persone, perché c’è il rischio di infezioni oculari.

“Ma davvero? Esistono delle infezioni oculari?”
“Accidenti, si! E sono diffusissime.”
“Che peccato… cavolo…”

Vi sono piaciuti i nostri consigli? O forse non usate occhiali da sole in primavera?

📸Фотографирую бесплатно? Кого, как и почему? 

Довольно часто мне приходят сообщения от моделей на счет сотрудничества с предложением “коллаборации”: это еще называется TFP или “творческая съемка”. И даже иногда я соглашаюсь на такой формат. В каких случаях я это могу сделать? 
 
💜мне очень нравится модель, а в свою очередь модели нравится моя идея\проект и она(он) готов на воплощение проекта во всех деталях: согласна с образом, локацией, условиями проведения съемки 
💜возможно, я соглашусь на “коллаборацию” с блоггером, аудитория которого мне действительно интересна. Если у вас 1 лям индусов в подписках - это еще не повод предлагать TFP. 
💜Если ко мне пришла модель\стилист\визажист и приглашают в крутой творческий проект, который подходит для моего портфолио 
👉во всех перечисленных случаях мы обговариваем и соглашаемся по всем пунктам: условия использования контента, количество публикаций в соцсетях, упоминания и т д. Подписываем соответствующие документы 
 
🙏TFP - это не бесплатная съемка и не халява для модели, это инвестирование моего времени и ресурсов и каждого члена команды (стилиста, визажиста, ассистента, ретушера и модели). И все это ради для создания кадров, которые займут достойное место в портфолио у каждого из нас. 
 
🙈Что не является бартером и не тянет на TFP, как бы этого ни хотелось: 
 
🍌“я вас отмечу, у меня хххх подписчиков” - дорогие мои, отметки не работают так, вы сами блоггеры и знаете это. Так слонятку не продать 🙂 
🍌“мы красивая портфолийная пара, хотим фото на фоне Дуомо” - с удовольствием, вы как раз моя ЦА, но для коммерческой съемки 
у меня (вставьте любое число) подписчиков, мне нужна всего одна фотка, я сделаю вам рекламу - опять же, вопрос к качеству вашей аудитории 
🍌“я модель, я приезжаю в Милан  завтра и хочу сделать фото, из одежды у меня майка шорты и кроссовки” - я буду рада поработать с хорошей моделью, но об образе стоит позаботиться заранее. Иначе это просто запрос на коммерцию. 
 
👇Дорогие коллеги, модели и все, кому есть чем поделиться: расскажите в комментариях о вашем опыте TFP, смешном и не очень🙏

🌈Stessa stagione eppure colori diversi?❤️‍🔥
.
Del tutto normale! Perchè siamo unici nei colori!
.
Ti dirò di più: oltre ad avere un mix cromatico univoco che può portare ad una palette personalizzata unica (fisica in tessuto o su file PDF.) potrai anche scegliere la nuova consulenza di armocromia "double season" (quindi ci incontreremo due volte nell'anno) per valutare anche come interagiscono i colori con la tua abbronzatura! Perchè anche quest'ultima è diversa da persona a persona..e magari siamo abbronzate più mesi all'anno!
.
Fermiamo inoltre insieme i falsi miti in cui la consulenza sul colore non si possa fare con l'abbronzatura! Anzi sfruttiamo questo cambiamento a nostro ulteriore vantaggio!
.
E se abbiamo già fatto una consulenza sul colore insieme, per ringraziarti della fiducia la parte di consulenza "da abbronzat*" avrà per te un prezzo scontato! (per prenotazioni entro settembre 2023).
.
Ti aspetto in dm per tutte le info!

#超鎖吻霧感唇釉
 
M·A•C帶著全新質地強勢回歸！！🔥
先跟各位報告這次新品#鎖吻唇釉 很可以收！🫡
 
水轉霧質地 剛上唇非常水潤很好抹開暈染
趁水潤的時候暈開然後就不要動等他乾 唇妝就會很完整服貼 薄塗也是很均勻不會斑駁😎
‼️大家記得看影片都有示範薄塗的妝效 真的不用怕顏色太飽和不好駕馭！！
 
成膜速度我覺得剛剛好
很夠拍開全唇 又不會等太久 基本上拍開之後等個5-10秒就差不多乾了
成膜後就固定住了 真的不沾杯 喝東西不會掉 持久度很好👍🏻
 
再來大重點 不會染唇🥺感動到要哭了吧？飽和持色卻用眼唇卸妝液就能輕鬆卸除
而且加了三重精油保濕配方 不會酸梅嘴
我連續試色八支 嘴巴還是舒服嫩嫩的而且沒有殘色
真的要給M•A•C新品頒獎狀😌
 
-
 
試色的八支中我的菜：
 
#91Emphatic #曖昧棕
暖烘烘的栗子土橘 很襯膚不挑皮
冬季裡開朗溫柔的鄰家女孩
 
#62Bodacious #迷醉粉
帶一點煙燻感的灰感豆沙色 神秘迷濛的氛圍感🌫️
酷酷質感女孩包包裡會有的顏色！
 
#67Meticulous #調情咖
比91更土調 試在手上的時候就讓我欲罷不能🤣
奶茶色就是百看不膩 低調好搭配 又有質感的日常實用色
 
#95Vicious #毒蘋果
比99更鮮艷明亮的純正蘋果色 真的有毒！
能提亮整個妝面 非常顯氣色 元氣滿滿的女主色🍎
 
#85Poncy #薄酒萊
這杯酒不只要讓你微醺 更要你大醉！
薄塗拍開來的帶紫調的血色感很漂亮 很顯白欸🍷
厚塗的暗紫紅 有種生人勿近的厭世距離感 暗黑系妝容很適合
 
#72MostCurious #野薔薇
薄塗也是好看⋯看影片了沒！！
很善良純真的嫩粉色🌸當打底增加唇部粉嫩感也可以喔！
 
#60MullitOver&Over #蜜桃裸
蜜桃櫻花粉 我上唇之後粉調蠻明顯的
時尚裸唇 當打底色也很百搭！
 
#99ExtraChili #魔鬼椒
濃郁紅棕 成熟霸氣的感覺
重要場合需要氣場的話選這支
薄塗也是很顯白><
 
結果發現八支都打完了🤣
快來留言告訴我哪支是你菜！！

#超鎖吻霧感唇釉 又稱 #鎖吻唇釉
主打獨創瞬效鎖色科技帶來的妝效 超長持色、防水、激吻也不會掉色🤣
（單身的我實測親杯子的確不沾～👍🏻）
是持久力非～常好的霧面唇彩就跟名字一樣 #鎖色鎖吻鎖潤澤
液化霧質地 剛塗上唇是一般唇釉質地 輕薄水潤
乾的速度很快 大概10秒左右就會變成霧面
我自己用了幾次之後 覺得最好上手的方法是
先塗在下唇再快速抿開 等待全乾！
就可以獲得一個漂亮的柔霧唇妝
如果想要顏色更濃郁就再塗一層
唇彩乾掉成膜之後 它就待在那不走了🤣
而且特別添加三重精油保濕配方
在嘴巴上整天都不會有緊繃感
喝水都不太掉 持久度很好
 
這系列的超級無敵顯色 深唇也能完全覆蓋住唇色
除了當唇彩之外 62、67、91當腮紅表現也很不錯
在臉上一樣很很持久
建議這系列要用「油」一點的眼唇卸妝液 可以輕鬆卸除
也可以用M·A·C的超奇肌清爽花瓣淨妝油 眼唇一起卸 這樣會更省力～
 
我最喜歡的色號：
#60 Mull it Over & Over 蜜桃裸
嫩嫩的裸粉色 淺色皮膚的日常首選
#67 Meticulous 調情咖
奶咖色 比60多了一點點棕調在裡面
一般膚色都可以駕馭
#99 Extra Chili 魔鬼椒
薄塗是復古的楓葉紅色
厚塗橘調會更多 整體顏色偏暖
 
其他的主打色號還有：
#72 Most Curiors
主打色裡面唯一一支偏粉色的
搭配粉嫩色系腮紅 好看！
#95 Vicious
乍看之下跟99很像 在嘴巴上的相似度也蠻高的
不過95更紅、明度也更高一些
這次的色彩都很日常耐用

現在#67 Meticulous 調情咖 
已經成為我每日包包裡必帶的唇釉！

即使是上了唇彩 也希望雙唇輕盈無負擔
超鎖吻霧感唇釉擁有三重精油保濕配方:百香果、椰子、乳木果油
能夠在日常讓嘴唇漂亮自然也同時保養

隨著要去的場合隨意變身

我覺得是比較適合正式場合或是喜歡完整妝容的人～

分享五色上唇後的感覺：

#60 Mull it Over & Over蜜桃裸 ✨
屬於偏橘的蜜桃裸色
適合淡妝日常找氣色 這支薄擦上護唇膏 
嘴巴看起來就像水嫩嫩的蜜桃🍑

#72 Most Curious 野薔薇 ✨
莓果色調的粉莓色
很適合白皮膚、夢幻氣質系女孩

#67 Meticulous 調情咖 ✨
這支是這次系列裡我最喜歡的顏色！
微微的紅色咖啡調
個人很喜歡咖啡色調的唇色
單擦就很顯氣色、看起來柔和氣質～

#99 Extra Chili 魔鬼椒 ✨
這次系列裡最喜歡的紅色調！
是屬於橘棕調性的紅
所以不論白皮黃皮黑皮都很適合
加上棕色的紅 有著更沈穩的氣質
感覺會是歐洲女孩人手一支的紅色💋

#95 Vicious 毒蘋果 ✨
喜歡正紅唇的人可以收的一色
非常的顯白！薄薄擦一層也會非常有氣色

全系列共有29個顏色
我喜歡把這幾個顏色混搭
邊玩邊化妝搭出一下適合自己的特別色

找出最適合自己的才是最重要的喔🫶🏻

最後，不染唇會不會不好卸？
防水且好卸的特點就是它很棒的地方～
搭配超奇肌清爽花瓣淨妝油，輕輕按摩後就乾淨無痕！

Sikkim's Eksha Kerung has yet again made her mark in the world of fashion as she becomes the face of Maybelline New York. Along with Shah Rukh Khan's daughter, Suhana Khan, Ananya Birla, and Olympic gold medalist PV Sindhu, Eksha's face will now grace the beauty brand's advertisements.

The shoot for Maybelline took place in both Bangkok and Mumbai, where Eksha completed her modelling session for the brand. The selection of the Sikkim girl by the agency reportedly came after they were looking for a face that has had an impact on society through their everyday life, and Eksha perfectly fit the bill.

Eksha is not just a model but is also a Sikkim Police cop and a finalist on MTV Supermodel of the Year Season 2. Apart from that, she has also been seen in a few acting projects. Her journey so far has been an inspiration to many, and her recent accomplishment with Maybelline New York only further cements her place in the world of fashion and modelling.

Maybelline New York, trading as Maybelline, is an American multinational cosmetics, skincare, fragrance, and personal care company, based in New York City. It was founded in Chicago in 1914 and has been a subsidiary of the French cosmetics company L'Oréal since 1996.

Daytime Makeup with a Wee Twist
---------------------------------------
Had a fab time teaching Catherine how to create a natural daytime look. And, as she loves a bright colour on her lips, we put a wee twist on the look with a bright pink lipstick 💄 

And with just a few makeup tips and tricks, she learned how to enhance her features and elevate her look. 

We used a combination of my kit and Catherine's to create this look. Catherine had a kit to rival any MUA's, and being a Beauty Pie lover, we used a lot of her products from them. And have to say I am growing to love this brand as well. More to follow on this!

Catherine not only achieved her makeup goals, but totally nailed the application as well! 💪

La primavera è la stagione della rinascita, dell'energia e della bellezza. 
E non c'è niente di più bello che immergersi in questo meraviglioso spettacolo della natura. Guardate questi colori vivaci, questi fiori magnifici che sbocciano ovunque intorno a noi, mentre i piccoli colibrì danzano leggiadri tra le corolle. Sono creature delicate, come la primavera stessa, che ci fanno sentire in pace con il mondo intero. La primavera ci riempie di gioia e speranza, e ci invita ad abbandonare ogni pensiero negativo, a lasciarci trasportare dalle emozioni più intense e a vivere ogni momento con il cuore aperto. Che la primavera ci insegni a cogliere la bellezza delle piccole cose, a gustare ogni istante della vita e a donare il nostro amore senza riserve.🌺

#꽃잎세럼 하이퍼 리얼 세라마이저TM 스킨 밸런싱 하이드레이션 세럼으로 
완벽한 피부 캔버스 만들어주기!

라이트풀 C+ 코랄 그라스 틴티드 프라이머로 들뜸 없는 피부 메이크업 완성~~
높은 자외선 차단 기능 덕분에 따로 자외선 차단제를 바를 필요 없어서 더 좋아요!

우선 기초가 탄탄해야 오래도록 메이크업이 유지되잖아요? 저는 맥의 <핑크톤업워터>와 <꽃잎세럼>으로 스킨케어를 쌓아주고 <로즈톤업베이스>로 마무리해주니 수분광 뿜뿜하는 빛나는 글로우 피부로 연출할 수 있었답니다 🫢 어떤 파운데이션을 발라도 밀림없이 고급스러운 피부표현 !! 넘 맘에들쟈냐

이렇게 이미 촉촉광 피부 완성이지만 버터처럼 녹아드는 립밤에 수채화처럼 맑게 채워지는 블러셔까지 함께 사용해주면 더 예쁘다구요 💗 곧 맥 글로우스택 립 제품들과 블러셔로 완성된 메이쿠업도 가져올예정이니 다음 포스팅도 기대해주세요! 꺄 설렌당 두근두근 코밍 쑨 🙋🏻📢❤️

102 weeks dye free // I just got hired for my first paid job as a professional makeup artist and I’m so excited to embark on this new career path. I used MAC skincare products on my face which is still healing from an #intensepulsedlight skin rejuvenation treatment 4 days ago. My cheeks are still a bit swollen and pink as this is where the most pigment was targeted due to dilated capillaries & sun damage. And yes, I’m absolutely not knowledgeable when it comes to makeup. Happy April Fool’s Day! I was just having fun with some MAC Cosmetics after work. I’m not adept at doing eye makeup at 53 so I often skip it for the most part, focusing on cheek and lip colors. I usually air dry my hair for beach waves but brushed it out to show the greys which are often hidden underneath my top hair layers. My hair gets so big when it’s brushed dry. 😆 I used #macstackmascara which is this week’s #mactrend #permedlashes .  My attempt at eyeshadow is weak but I was just having fun experimenting with colors I usually wear separately #macallthatglitters and #macembark . The purple eyeshadow was my first ever MAC purchase years ago as a MUA told me to just use it as a soft eyeliner using a thin brush since I told him that I’m makeup challenged. It actually looks quite neutral on an otherwise bare lid. Happy April 1. Enjoy this life cause you only get one. Don’t be afraid to look foolish along the way. #makeitMAC #macglowplay #macsonatural #macsweettreat #macstudioradiance #machyperrealserumizer #machyperreal #silversisters #grombre #saltandpepperhair #openlygrey

📚 Black educational reads 📚

As a Black educator, it’s important that I understand the history of Black educational experiences. I advise the best students in my city, all while they are constantly fighting injustices and systemic racism inside their schools. Here are some of my favorite reads about the movement that I recommend 💯

1️⃣ The Education of Black People by W.E.B. DuBois

2️⃣ Sing a Rhythm, Dance a Blues: Liberatory Education for Black and Brown Girls by Monique W. Morris

3️⃣ Brown vs. Board of Education: A Civil Rights Milestone and its Troubled Legacy by James T. Patterson

We are so grateful to the George C. Hall branch of the @chicagopubliclibrary for hosting us last week for our first public event on our Black Nurses in Chicago Project!

The Hall branch (located in Bronzeville on Chicago's Southside) has been displaying our exhibit for the last two weeks. 

On Saturday, April 1, Dr. Karen Flynn, the co-PI on the Black Nurses project, presented the project to members of the community and engaged in conversations with them about these stories. This was a particularly meaningful location because much of the Black nursing history in our project, including both sites of Provident Hospital, has been centered just minutes away from the Hall branch.

Plus, some of our oral history participants showed up to join the discussion! See Dr. Fred Brown, shown in the second photo with Dr. Flynn in front of the exhibit.

We are still looking for additional sites to host our exhibit - especially in predominantly Black neighborhoods of Chicago. Feel free to send us a private message or email: lmince2@uic.edu if you are interested in hosting the exhibit or a talk or both!

THE BUST OF NEFERTITI, QUEEN OF EGYPT 

In 1912, a German archaeological team led by Ludwig Borchardt found in the workshop of Thutmose (an ancient Egyptian sculptor) in Armana, Egypt, a bust of Nefertiti, the Great Royal Wife & possible co-regent of Akhenaten, 14th century BCE Pharaoh of Egypt.  The bust, thought to have been crafted by Thutmose in 1345 BCE, is made of limestone & coated with stucco layers. In March 2009, @time listed the bust amongst the "Top 10 Plundered Artifacts.” 

A 1924 document written by the Secretary of the German Oriental Company told of a 1913 meeting between Borchardt & Gustave Lefebvre (a French Egyptologist & Egypt’s Chief Antiques Inspector) to discuss division of the 1912 archeological finds between Egypt & Germany. According to the Secretary, Borchardt "wanted to save the bust for us.”Borchardt has been accused of hiding the bust's real value by showing Lefebvre a photograph of the bust "that didn't show Nefertiti in her best light,” wrapping it up in a box when Lefebvre came to inspect, & claiming it was made of gypsum. However, the German Oriental Company blamed Lefebvre for  negligence. 

Since its official unveiling in Berlin in 1924, Egypt has demanded its return. Notably, in 1933 Hermann Göring considered returning it to King Farouk I of Egypt but Adolf Hitler opposed the idea describing the bust as "a unique masterpiece, an ornament, a true treasure" & declaring that he would build a new Egyptian museum for Nefertiti. Also notably, when the US controlled parts of Germany after World War 2, it declined a request from Egypt for the bust’s return.

The bust is one of the most admired and copied images from ancient Egypt, the star exhibit for marketing Berlin's museums, and an international icon of beauty.

COLLABORATION | RYAN COSBERT/ARTMATCH

Last month, we had the incredible chance with Anthony Roberts @anthony.c.roberts and @artmatch_art_advisory to interview Ryan Cosbert @bcosryan , an amazing Abstract painter based in New York, NY, USA. 

Cosbert’s work is rooted in research. She deeply explores a topic and carefully chooses her medium before composing it on canvas or paper. Her formal and self-guided education informs her creative practice, grounding it in formal principles with a fresh take on a variety of topics. Centering her subject matter on the African diaspora, Cosbert aims to create beautiful works that also spark curiosity about the inspiration behind them, thus leading to deeper levels of cultural awareness and spiritual development. In her budding career, Cosbert has had a number of successful exhibitions including her most recent solo exhibition at UTA Artist Space. She also just completed a residency program in London with PM/AM Gallery, in Mayfair, and currently has a group show with them.

Yeah, you’re reading that right: This is how Black models MADE their own foundation. 

It’s also an intimate glimpse into the backstage scene of the Ebony Fashion Fair, a traveling fashion show started in 1958 by the co-founder of EBONY and JET magazine, Eunice Johnson.  Some women were being pinned into their dresses, but others concocted their own foundations by crushing up eye makeup and powder foundation. 

Makeup brands rarely made foundation for darker-skinned people; if you got lucky, you found a Black makeup brand that carried your shade, usually accessible via mail order.  But all of this took time and labor, hoping you’d find a brand that cared enough to think your skin color mattered.  White women, on the other hand, could go to their local department store, or meet up with a makeup artist—they had a plethora of options. 

Beautifying yourself as a non-white woman in America always meant expending more time, labor, and resources.  Beauty critics lament the labor involved in fitting cisheterosexual beauty norms, but rarely talk about how this labor isn’t evenly distributed among all women.  The playing field isn’t fair, and never has been.

Eunice Johnson attempted to improve these odds, however.  Watching women creating their own foundation backstage, she decided to create her own makeup brand.  In 1973, she created Fashion Fair Cosmetics, catering to makeup’s most ignored demographic, the Black woman.  And she managed to get her brand in department stores too.

What challenges have you faced with makeup if you’re BIPoC? 
___________
(📸 Ebony Fashion Fair Archive.  I think it’s model Marie Chalk from 1968.)

“It must all be done in darkness…” is an intimate and immersive, experimental experience centered on Harriet Jacobs. A writer, abolitionist, and survivor, Jacobs spent seven years in isolation before escaping to Massachusetts and earning her freedom. Through film, movement, audience participation, and music, this world premiere opera celebrates Jacobs and her story of perseverance. A story that begs for us to learn, grow, and heal.

John Lee Johnson (1941–2006) 

Mr. Johnson grew up in Champaign-Urbana and become an influential leader and community advocate. In 1967, he helped organize the Special Education Opportunities Program and Project 500 at the University of Illinois, which sought to increase the school's enrollment of Black and Latinx students. 

He served as a member of the Champaign City Council from 1973–1981. Additionally, he contributed to the development of Champaign's Martin Luther King Jr. Subdivision. Over his lifetime, he received many awards and accolades for his contributions.

In 2006, the Champaign City Council designated Fourth Street (between University and Bradley Avenues) as Honorary John Lee Johnson Way. Then, in 2020, the Champaign City Council announced that the clubhouse in the Bristol Place Residences would also be named after John Lee Johnson.

[Written by: Gabriel Scott] 

Actor, Johnny Depp, has an interesting ancestry tracing back to his 8th great-grandmother, Elizabeth Grinstead of Virginia. She was the first Black person in American colonies to sue for their freedom and win in 1656. Elizabeth married a White lawyer named, William Grinstead and had a child together. With William being a lawyer, he defended Elizabeth and their child in the court case. With their child being the primary subject, the case was based on the status of the father. After their victory, the laws changed to where cases were based on the status of the mother. Many Black women at the time were slaves which made it difficult to be granted freedom. White men having babies with Black women was common, but Black men having babies with White women was pretty rare at the time.  #AMERICAN HISTORY #REAL FACTS #GRINSTEAD #DEPP

Last month, Pittsburgh lost veteran newsman George Barbour, seen here interviewing marchers during the Pittsburgh Peace March on April 7, 1968. Barbour was the first Black radio reporter in Pittsburgh (working for KDKA) and also holds the distinction of being the only Black reporter at the Selma, Alabama march in 1965 . A graduate of the @pittofficial, Barbour’s award-winning career spanned several decades.

Public service announcement:

The Lincoln-Coles Archive on @internetarchive contains yearbooks, commencement programs, student publications, and other ephemera related to Lincoln High School and R.T. Coles Vocational and Junior High School covering the period prior to the 1955/1956 academic year.

The archive developed as a research tool for the @myrtle_and_ollie project. Hugh Oliver Cook served at Lincoln High School as a teacher, vice-principal, and principal from 1901 through 1943. Myrtle Foster Cook taught at the school from 1912 through 1915. Understanding the history of that institution is an essential component for understanding Cooks professional lives.

No single institution in Kansas City – not even Lincoln College Preparatory Academy, as today’s Lincoln High School is known – held an entire set of Lincoln High School yearbooks. So I started collecting and scanning yearbooks and other school related items. I appreciate institutions where I have been privileged to serve in some capacity for their assistance. But I am particularly grateful to alumni of Lincoln and Coles for contributing items for scanning. Providing free access to the materials through @internetarchive is one way I can express that gratitude.

The Lincoln-Coles Archive is a collective effort. For example, one alumna may have one issue of the Lincolnite school newspaper, another alumnus has a different issue, and the grandchild of a Lincoln graduate has yet another issue. The Archive provides a way to assemble the different pieces that together start to create a bigger picture of the whole.

Anyway, thought this might be of interest to some folks following this account. Go to archive.org and search Lincoln-Coles Archive.

I am always looking for additional items to (slowly) add. DM me if you wish to contribute.

Public service announcement:

The Lincoln-Coles Archive on @internetarchive contains yearbooks, commencement programs, student publications, and other ephemera related to Lincoln High School and R.T. Coles Vocational and Junior High School covering the period prior to the 1955/1956 academic year.

The archive developed as a research tool for the Cook biography project. If you've been following along, you know Hugh Oliver Cook served at Lincoln High School as a teacher, vice-principal, and principal from 1901 through 1943. Myrtle Foster Cook taught at Lincoln from 1912 through 1915. Understanding the history of that institution is an essential component for understanding the couple’s professional lives.

No single institution in Kansas City – not even Lincoln College Preparatory Academy, as today’s Lincoln High School is known – held an entire set of Lincoln High School yearbooks. So I started collecting and scanning yearbooks and other school related items. I appreciate institutions where I have been privileged to serve in some capacity for their assistance. But I am particularly grateful to alumni of Lincoln and Coles for contributing items for scanning. Providing free access to the materials through @internetarchive is one way I can express that gratitude.

The Lincoln-Coles Archive is a collective effort. For example, one alumna may have one issue of the Lincolnite school newspaper, another alumnus has a different issue, and the grandchild of a Lincoln graduate has yet another issue. The Archive provides a way to assemble the different pieces that together start to create a bigger picture of the whole.

Anyway, thought this might be of interest to some folks following this account. Go to archive.org and search Lincoln-Coles Archive.

I am always looking for additional items to (slowly) add. DM me if you wish to contribute.

With the Audubon building facing demolition in the 1990s, Dr. Betty Shabazz and the grassroots community organized and advocated to preserve the site as a Memorial to Malcolm X, and continued his efforts in civic engagement and community organizing.

Next Monday (4/17) marks 30 years since Ellen Ochoa first went into space. Her career started as an innovative engineer and she went on to become the first Hispanic woman astronaut. Since then she has logged nearly 1,000 hours in space and won many awards for her success. 

Now, at age 64, she is director of NASA's Johnson Space Center, the second woman to hold the title and the first Latina.

CHINA  DREADLOCKS FROM 35,000 BC!
These are African Chinese, known as the Jomon people, and it is assumed that the original inhabitants of China were black. They arrived 100,000 years ago and were still living in the country during the Qing Dynasty. Rocking their natural hair way back in the early 20th century!

At about 35,000 B.C. some of these people took this route and entered Japan, they became the first Humans to inhabit the Japanese Islands. Later, another group, known to us as the Ainu, followed.Today, their genes can still be found in 40% of modern Japanese, as well as Mongolians and Tibetans- Past and Present Kings & Queens.

My body barely grazes hers, just enough to make her crave my touch. She doesn’t turn around but continues to look into the darkness. 

“Simone, we need to talk.” I’m worried she’s going to give me the silent treatment. Simone rarely displays anger, but she will stop talking, and that’s much worse.

She’s quiet for a minute. “We do,” she finally says.

I’m nervous to start the conversation, because I've successfully avoided this topic for a while now. I knew this day would come, and I’ve dreaded it. “Do you want to tell me what happened back there?” I ask.

“I don’t know. My hands just got hot, and I couldn’t control it.”

“Not that, Simone. What’s your problem?”

“I’m sure you figured it out by now,” Simone said.

“Figured what out? This is your problem. You need to stop being passive aggressive and tell me what’s on your mind.”

“I want to get married, obviously.”

“If you wanted to get married that badly, why didn’t you say anything?” 

“I don’t know, Wade.”

“You do know. Stop avoiding the issue and be real with me.”

“Are you going to pretend that you weren’t avoiding the issue as well?”

“I’m not the one with the problem.”

“You are the one with the problem. I want you to want to marry me because you love me. I shouldn’t have to tell you that.”

“I’ve never seen you that upset before.”

“No, you haven’t.”

“You hold a lot in. You can’t 
do that to me, princess. We have to communicate.”

“Because you’re so good at communicating.”

“When it comes to you I’m willing to try.”

“Very well then. Let’s communicate. Wade, I want to get married. I want to have kids. I want to be a family.”

“Finally, you say it. Was that so bad?”

“I don’t know. How do you feel about all that? Communicate with me.”

I sigh. “I’m not ready.”
